dc_description_s: This polyline shapefile depicts centerlines of Streets in the County of Humboldt, California, including all public and some private roads, street names and zip codes. The Roadway Functional Class attribute is based on the Humboldt County Travel Demand Forecasting Model.The Humboldt County Planning and Building Department is responsible for protecting the public health, safety and welfare via building permit review and inspections consistent with California model codes as well as planning and development review and approval consistent with the county's General Plan. This Department oversees the Advance Planning Division, which is responsible for the Humboldt County's Geographic Information System (GIS) that is utilized by other County Departments; many federal, state and local agencies; and the general public. This coverage can be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analyses of geospatial data.
dc_publisher_s: Humboldt County Planning and Building Department
